name: Vega-C | Pléiades Neo 5 & 6

status.name: Launch Failure
status.description: Either the launch vehicle did not reach orbit, or the payload(s) failed to separate.

net_precision.name: Second
net_precision.description: The T-0 is accurate to the second.

failreason: 2nd stage Zefiro 40 motor lost chamber pressure from T+151 seconds due to unexpected erosion of carbon-carbon (C-C) material in the motor nozzle's throat insert, caused by the material's flaw in homogeneity.

mission.name: Pléiades Neo 5 & 6
mission.description: Pléiades Neo 5 and 6 are the last two in a constellation of four optical high-resolution Earth observation satellites built and operated by Airbus. It is a dual purpose constellation, serving both civilian and military purposes.

pad.name: Ariane Launch Area 1 (ELV)
pad.description: ELA-1, now named Ensemble de Lancement Vega (short ELV), is a launch pad at the Centre Spatial Guyanais in French Guiana. It has been used to support launches of the Europa rocket, Ariane 1, Ariane 3, and is currently used to launch Vega rockets.

location.name: Guiana Space Centre, French Guiana
location.description: The Guiana Space Centre is a European spaceport to the northwest of Kourou in French Guiana, a region of France in South America. Kourou is located at a latitude of 5°. In operation since 1968, it is a suitable location for a spaceport because of its equatorial location and open sea to the east.
